  "text": "and miR-206 has also been shown to promote myoblast differentiation [CITATION_1] 38 . Our group reported that miR148a could promote myogenic differentiation by repressing the ROCK1 39 . The miRNAs represent a newly recognized level of regulation of gene expression mediating skeletal muscle development. However, the function of miRNAs in skeletal muscle development and phenotypic variance has remained largely unclear.",
